author: Alex Carrion

text: @Alex Carrion Yes, but you could extend that argument to ever-broader generalizations that lose more meaning with each step. The statement that would make more sense would be "Masanori Adachi and Taro Kudo knew how to do music", or, if JimmyLovesGamesTV meant Konami's composers in general, then "Konami's composers knew how to do music".
author: D.E. McKnight

text: +JimmyLovesGamesTV Well, that's not exactly fair to say. I mean sure, Adachi and Kudo are fantastic composers and Super Castlevania IV has one of the best OST's out there, but there are plenty of other 16-bit games that have excellent music as well. Mitsuda (Chrono Trigger), Uematsu (Final Fantasy VI) and Sakuraba (Tales of Phantasia) totally compare with this.
